This is absolutely divine. I make it regularly. I usually substitute two slices of bacon for the prosciutto because I always have it on hand. I love it with seared scallops or crab on top. It goes together in the time it takes to bring the pasta water to a boil. A quick meal that tastes like you worked for hours.

Rating: 4
This was a nice change from other creamy pasta dishes--and SO easy. A couple of thoughts: while I think browning the prosciutto was definitely warranted, there's no need to use butter--just a nonstick pan. I removed it before boiling the sauce and added it in at the end w/ the cheese and remaining zest. I didn't have fresh pasta, but at least used a high-quality dried egg noodle. Per another reviewer, I doubled the prosciutto...which was a bit too much. Next time, maybe 1-1/2 times, and up the orange zest/juice accordingly. I also added toasted pine nuts, which I though worked well, and could see where peas would up the veggie quotient w/o corrupting the light orange flavor.

